article.description: Pryor scores 25, leads Robert Morris over Duquesne 75-59
article.headline: Pryor scores 25, leads Robert Morris over Duquesne 75-59
article.linkText: Pryor scores 25, leads Robert Morris over Duquesne 75-59
article.story: MOON TOWNSHIP, Pa. -- Rodney Pryor scored 25 points, Kavon Stewart had 12 points and dished out a career-best 11 assists, and Robert Morris rolled to a 75-59 victory over Duquesne on Saturday. Pryor scored 14 points in the first half to help Robert Morris build a 39-30 halftime lead. In the second, Derrick Colter drained back-to-back 3-pointers to pull Duquesne within 46-42 with 15:47 to play. The Colonials answered with a 14-0 run to stretch their lead to 60-42 with 9:52 remaining and led by double digits the rest of the way. Elijah Minnie matched career-highs with 10 points and 10 rebounds, and Marcquise Reed chipped in 10 points for Robert Morris (3-6). Colter and Eric James each scored 17 points to lead Duquesne (3-4), which shot just 19 of 61 for 31.1 percent from the field.
